SENATE BILL No. 256
_____
DIGEST OF SB 256 (Updated January 20, 2026 3:52 pm - DI 106)
Citations Affected: IC 4-6.
Synopsis: Foreign agent registration and foreign terrorist
organizations. Requires certain persons acting on behalf of a hostile
foreign country to register with the attorney general. Establishes a
procedure to deny state benefits to persons who aid a foreign terrorist
organization.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Garten, Koch, Freeman, Busch,
Baldwin
January 8, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Judiciary.
January 15, 2026, reported favorably — Do Pass.
January 20, 2026, read second time, amended, ordered engrossed.
SB 256—LS 6708/DI 106

