1 government of a hostile foreign country, a nonresident alien
2 of a hostile foreign country, or an entity organized under the
3 laws of, or having its principal place of business in, a hostile
4 foreign country.
5 Sec. 8. As used in this chapter, "political activity" means an
6 activity that is performed with the intent to influence:
7 (1) a state or local governmental entity, agency, or public
8 official in Indiana; or
9 (2) the general public in Indiana;
10 concerning the formulation, adoption, or modification of the laws
11 or policies of the state, or the election or opposition to the election
12 of a candidate for state or local office.
13 Sec. 9. (a) This section applies to an agent. Before acting as an
14 agent, a person who acts as an agent shall file with the attorney
15 general a true and complete registration statement in addition to
16 supplements as required.
17 (b) The registration statement must include the following:
18 (1) The registrant's name.
19 (2) The registrant's principal business address, and all other
20 business addresses in the United States or elsewhere.
21 (3) The registrant's residential addresses, if any.
22 (4) If the registrant is an individual, the registrant's
