6
1 (1) The name of the foreign supported political organization,
2 its business address, and the names, titles, and addresses of all
3 officers and directors of the foreign supported political
4 organization.
5 (2) If the foreign supported political organization is affiliated
6 with or is a chapter of a national organization, the name of the
7 national organization, its address, and the names and
8 addresses of its officers and directors.
9 (3) A detailed statement of any expenditures of money or
10 anything of value made by the organization within the prior
11 calendar year for the purpose of political activity.
12 (4) A detailed statement of all money or anything of value
13 received by the organization from a hostile foreign principal
14 or an agent during the preceding calendar year.
15 (c) A registrant must update the information required under
16 subsection (b) at least once every quarter.
17 (d) A foreign supported political organization shall pay a fee of
18 five hundred dollars ($500) at the time the agent files an initial
19 registration statement under this section.
20 (e) A fee established by the attorney general in accordance with
21 this chapter must accompany an application for registration or
22 renewal of registration.
23 (f) Failure to comply with subsections (a) through (c) is a
