25 Sec. 11. It is a violation of this chapter if a person or agent:
26 (1) submits a registration statement required to be filed under
27 this chapter that is materially incorrect;
28 (2) fails to file a corrected registration statement or report
29 after being requested to do so by the attorney general; or
30 (3) fails to make a filing required by section 9 or section 10 of
31 this chapter.
32 Sec. 12. (a) Whenever the attorney general has reasonable cause
33 to believe a person or entity may be an affiliate of a foreign
34 terrorist organization, the attorney general may exercise all
35 existing civil investigative powers, including the issuance of civil
36 investigative demands, to determine whether the entity is an
37 affiliate of a foreign terrorist organization.
38 (b) If the attorney general determines, based on the attorney
39 general's investigation, that a person or entity is an affiliate of a
40 foreign terrorist organization, the attorney general shall notify the
41 person or entity of the attorney general's determination and
42 provide the entity with thirty (30) days in which to submit a formal
SB 256—LS 6708/DI 106

7
1 response to the attorney general's determination.
2 (c) The attorney general shall provide the attorney general's
3 determination, the evidence on which it is based, and the person's
4 or entity's response to the governor.
5 Sec. 13. The governor shall designate a person or entity as an
6 affiliate of a foreign terrorist organization if the governor
7 concludes, based on a review of the results of the investigation
8 conducted by the attorney general under section 12 of this chapter
9 and the person's or entity's formal response, that the evidence
10 amassed by the attorney general demonstrates that it is more likely
11 than not that the person or entity is an affiliate of a foreign
12 terrorist organization.
13 Sec. 14. (a) Any person or entity that is designated an affiliate
14 of a foreign terrorist organization shall:
15 (1) be denied all state funds provided by any state agency,
16 including:
17 (A) funding;
18 (B) benefits; or
19 (C) other forms of support;
20 received or provided, directly or indirectly, from the state;
21 (2) be prohibited from entering into any contract with the
22 state; and
23 (3) be denied any:
24 (A) employment;
25 (B) tax benefit;
26 (C) privilege; or
27 (D) other form of a state benefit or privilege, whether
28 provided or received directly or indirectly.
29 (b) No public university, community college, school district, or
30 other recipient of state funds may, after the date of the governor
31 designates that a person or entity is an affiliate of a foreign
32 terrorist organization under section 13 of this chapter, knowingly
33 provide a grant, contract, loan, tax credit, tax exemption, or other
34 financial benefit to an affiliate of a foreign terrorist organization.
35 Sec. 15. (a) A designation under section 13 of this chapter
36 remains in effect until rescinded by the governor.
37 (b) The governor shall rescind a designation under section 13 of
38 this chapter only if:
39 (1) the governor determines that the designation was
40 erroneous; or
41 (2) the governor determines that the actions of the person or
42 entity that support the designation occurred more than five
SB 256—LS 6708/DI 106

8
1 (5) years ago.
2 Sec. 16. (a) If the attorney general has reasonable cause to
3 believe a violation of this chapter has occurred, the attorney
4 general may bring an action in the name of the state in connection
5 with a violation of this chapter to seek:
6 (1) appropriate injunctive or other equitable relief;
7 (2) the costs and expenses of the suit, including reasonable
8 attorney's fees and expert fees; and
9 (3) a civil penalty of not more than five hundred dollars
10 ($500).
11 (b) If a violation of this chapter is committed intentionally, or
12 constitutes a second or subsequent violation, the attorney general
13 may bring a civil action to recover a civil penalty of not more than
14 ten thousand dollars ($10,000) per violation, in addition to the
15 relief provided in subsection (a)(1) and (a)(2).
16 (c) A civil penalty collected under this chapter shall be deposited
17 in the state general fund.
18 Sec. 17. The attorney general may adopt rules under IC 4-22-2
19 to carry out this chapter.
